# 4. 背中を押せるように

Haruka: (Alright, now that I've bought souvenirs for Miku and the others, I should be good.)
Haruka: (How is everyone... Hm?)
Haruka: Hoshino, is everything okay? You look troubled.
Ichika: Oh, Kiritani. Actually, I'm struggling to decide which souvenir to get.
Ichika: I have a friend who tutors me on singing, but I'm not sure what to get for her...
Haruka: I see. Does she also play in a band?
Ichika: Oh, no. She's actually a PXL cast member. She's an absolutely amazing singer.
Ichika: She's taught me so much, so I'd really like to get her something nice...
Ichika: *Sigh* After that bath, I feel like I can finally relax.
Ichika: We actually had our first solo show... And yet, it doesn't feel like it's fully over.
Ichika: Hm? Someone's calling me...
Ichika: Kusanagi? I wonder why she's calling me this late.
Ichika: Hello. Kusanagi?
Nene: <Oh, hi... Sorry for calling this late.>
Ichika: No, it's alright. I just got out of the bath and was about to have some barley tea.
Nene: <Hehe, I see. Make sure to keep warm.>
Nene: <Um, Hoshino... Congratulations on your first solo show. You sang so well.>
Nene: <All of the things you and your bandmates wanted to convey really came through. So...I was really moved by your performance.>
Ichika: I'm glad. It makes me so happy hearing that from you, Kusanagi.
Ichika: Also... I think you're part of the reason today went well.
Nene: <What?>
Ichika: You've been helping me with my singing all this time, right? Thanks to that, I've been able to improve... And that's what kept me working hard for this solo show.
Ichika: So, thank you very much.
Nene: <...>
Ichika: Kusanagi?
Nene: <Oh, sorry. It's nothing.>
Nene: <But hearing you sing...made me want to try harder too.>
Ichika: Huh?
Nene: <The way you sang with such confidence up there today was so cool...>
Nene: <It made me think, “Wow, my friend is amazing.” After that, I felt like I should be more brave.>
Nene: <It made me want to work harder, so that I can stand on stage the same way you did.>
Ichika: Kusanagi...
Nene: <Sorry for dumping all of that out of nowhere. That was weird.>
Ichika: No, not at all. Let's both keep working hard.
Haruka: I see... So you're hoping to find a gift for her.
Ichika: Yes. I was thinking of getting her something that can be a sign of my support...
Haruka: Something that can give her support...
Haruka: Oh, how about something matching?
Ichika: Something matching? Like a keychain?
Haruka: Yes. You know, I think a reminder that she's not alone would help her have courage whenever she's feeling anxious.
Haruka: A fan once told me how concert merch had that effect on them.
Ichika: Concert merch?
Haruka: Yes. They said the matching merch they bought with their friend cheers them up because it reminds them of that shared memory.
Ichika: I see... I think I can understand where they're coming from. Saki has said something similar before.
Ichika: In that case, I'll get her something we can have a pair of.
Ichika: I wonder what would be good...
Ichika: (This little blue bird...)
Ichika: (I remember Kusanagi mentioning that the main character of this musical she recommended treasured something like this...)
Haruka: That looks good. They would be cute as a pair.
Ichika: I think so too! I'll go with these little blue bird keychains.
Ichika: Thank you, Kiritani. I'm glad I was able to pick something nice.
Haruka: I hope your friend likes it.
???: Hey! It's Haruka!
Haruka: Huh?
Elementary Schooler on a Field Trip: The girl wearing glasses?
Elementary Schooler on a Field Trip: You're right! It's Haruka Kiritani!
Ichika: Uh oh, what should we do? At this rate, people are going to start gathering...
Ichika: Kiritani, this way—
Haruka: Wait, Hoshino.
Ichika: What?
Elementary Schooler on a Field Trip: *Gasp* Haruka's coming this way! I'm gonna ask for an autograph!
Elementary Schooler on a Field Trip: What? You don't even have anything she can write on! Let's just shake her hand!
Haruka: Hello. I see that you were able to see through my disguise. Well done.
Elementary Schooler on a Field Trip: I could tell it was you straight away since you're so pretty!
Haruka: Hehe, thank you. It makes me happy hearing that.
Haruka: But I have a favor to ask all of you. Would you mind listening?
Elementary Schooler on a Field Trip: Really? What is it, what is it?
Haruka: The thing is... I'm actually in the middle of a game of hide and seek.
Haruka: I don't want anyone to know where I'm hiding, so... Could you all please keep my location a secret for me?
Elementary Schooler on a Field Trip: I didn't know that! Okay, my lips are sealed!
Elementary Schooler on a Field Trip: But as a trade, can I shake your hand?
Haruka: Hehe, of course.
Elementary Schooler on a Field Trip: Me too, me too! Can I have an autograph?
Elementary School Teacher: Alright everyone, that's enough—
Haruka: Oh, it's okay.
Haruka: I don't have a pen or paper, so I won't be able to sign autographs...but if you wait quietly and patiently, I can take turns shaking your hands?
Elementary Schooler on a Field Trip: Okay!
Ichika: Kiritani...
Haruka: Sorry about this, Hoshino. I know Tenma and the others will worry if we don't get going soon.
Haruka: Oh, I know. Could you go ahead first? I'll meet up with you after this.
Ichika: (Kiritani's amazing... She's an idol even in a place like this.)
Ichika: Okay. I'll wait for you with the others.
Haruka: Thank you, Hoshino.
Haruka: Alright, so who's first?
